g.text: Tool 1: Polyline (The Connector)
What it does: Draws lines between points you specify
Like: Playing connect-the-dots
Practical use: Making graphs, drawing borders
Technical detail: Uses (x,y) coordinates for each point
Tool 2: Polymarker (The Spotter)
What it does: Puts symbols (★, +, •) at specific locations
Like: Dropping pins on a Google Map
Practical use: Showing data points on charts
Technical detail: You control symbol type and size
Tool 3: Fill Area (The Painter)
What it does: Colors in any shape you define
Like: Using the paint bucket tool in Photoshop
Practical use: Creating colored bars in bar charts
Technical detail: Can use solid colors or patterns
Tool 4: Text (The Writer)
What it does: Adds words to your graphics
Like: Typing labels on a diagram
Practical use: Axis labels on graphs
Technical detail: Controls font, size, and angle
